{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\nBuild a 5 V four-transistor NMOS cascode current mirror. The input/reference side is a stacked diode-connected NMOS branch that generates two bias voltages. The output side is a matched stacked NMOS branch that mirrors the reference current into a resistive load connected to `VDD`.\n\n**Device/Function List**\n- `VDD`: independent DC supply, `VDD` to `0`, value `5 V`.\n- `IREFSRC`: independent DC current source from `VDD` to `Iref`, value `100uA`.\n- `R`: load resistor from `VDD` to `Iout`, value `10k`.\n- `M1`: reference bottom NMOS, diode-connected with `drain=gate=nref_mid`, `source=0`, `bulk=0`.\n- `M2`: reference cascode/top NMOS, diode-connected with `drain=gate=Iref`, `source=nref_mid`, `bulk=nref_mid`.\n- `M3`: output bottom NMOS mirror device, `drain=nout_mid`, `gate=nref_mid`, `source=0`, `bulk=0`.\n- `M4`: output cascode/top NMOS, `drain=Iout`, `gate=Iref`, `source=nout_mid`, `bulk=nout_mid`.\n- NMOS model: LEVEL 1 NMOS, `VTO≈0.6 V`, `KP=100u`, devices sized `W=50u`, `L=1u`.\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\n`IREFSRC` forces `100uA` from `VDD` into `Iref`, through the diode-connected reference stack `M2-M1` to ground. This self-biases:\n- `nref_mid`: gate bias for bottom mirror devices `M1/M3`.\n- `Iref`: gate bias for cascode devices `M2/M4`.\n\nBulks should be tied to sources to avoid unwanted body effect.\n\n**Signal Or Feedback Path**\nThe reference stack provides local diode-connected feedback: `M1` regulates `nref_mid`, and `M2` regulates `Iref`. These two voltages are copied to the output stack gates, causing `M3/M4` to sink approximately the same current as the reference branch, limited by output compliance and the `10k` load.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n- Final filename should be `p17.cir`.\n- Preserve node names exactly: `Iref` and `Iout`.\n- Include only `.op` analysis.\n- Do not use subcircuits or placeholders.\n- Use explicit independent source line equivalent to: `IREFSRC VDD Iref DC 100uA`.\n- `Iout` must be the node shared by `R` bottom terminal and `M4` drain.\n- `Iref` must be the node shared by `IREFSRC` output, `M2` drain, `M2` gate, and `M4` gate.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n- Do not reverse `IREFSRC`; it must force current from `VDD` into `Iref`.\n- Do not omit diode connections on `M1` and `M2`.\n- Do not tie `M2` or `M4` bulk to ground; tie each to its source node.\n- Do not rename `Iref` or `Iout`.\n- Do not connect `R` to an internal node such as `nout_mid`; it belongs from `VDD` to `Iout`.\n- Ensure output branch has enough voltage headroom; otherwise `.op` may show reduced mirror current or one output transistor leaving saturation."}}
